@NODE "cable" "Parallel nullmodem cable"
@TOC "MAIN"
Parallel nullmodem-cable:

	It is a cable which is used for example to exchange data between PC's. 
	Not all Pins are connected and some of them are crossed. To use 
	Easylink all you need is a nullmodem-cable which is commonly used in 
	the PC World. 
	
	How to make your own parallel nullmodem-cable:
	
	You need two male 25pole SUB-D-plugs and a single screened
	cable with 10 wires, which is not longer than 3 m.
	
		
    The following pins must be connected:
		
    Pin             Pin
			
    2---------------15
    3---------------13
    4---------------12	
    5---------------10          Look at the graphic "Interface.iff"
    6---------------11          to see the numbers of the pins on the
    10---------------5          plugs.
    11---------------6
    12---------------4	
    13---------------3
    15---------------2
    
    
    If you are not able or not willing to make a cable and you cannot
    buy one, @{"contact me by E-Mail or mail" LINK "Addr1"}.

	
@ENDNODE

